> We love a classic pizza night, but tonight we'll have to ask the tomato sauce to step aside—there's a new kid in town. You'll slather crispy flatbreads with a rich, savory Vidalia onion cream sauce we just can't get enough of. Add tender, golden brown zucchini and earthy mushrooms, top it with a lemon-kissed arugula salad for bright contrast, and that's it. Simple, satisfying, and all in 25 minutes—a hearty vegetarian dinner idea you just can't pass up!

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drop @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}(in packets) into a #small bowl{} of warm water to soften.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce}(trimmed and thinly sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Bake until golden brown and crispy, ~{7-9%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between two sheets; toast on top and middle racks.)

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and zucchini; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Set aside.

Remove cream cheese packets from #bowl{}; discard water and wipe bowl dry. Combine cream cheese and @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce} in same bowl; whisk until smooth and creamy.

Place @arugula{2%ounce} and tomato in a #large bowl{}. Add juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings) and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} (large drizzle for 4). Season with pepper and toss to combine.

Evenly spread flatbreads with Vidalia cream and top with veggies.

Cut into squares and divide between plates; top with arugula salad. Serve.